<statement>
<p>Which of the following is largest amount (rather than largest percent)? </p>
<p><ol style="list-style-type:upper-alpha"><li>95<percent/> of 39</li> 
<li>38<percent/> of 213</li> 
<li>2<percent/> of 2488</li> 
</ol></p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>B: 38<percent/> of 213</li></ul></p><p>We must first calculate (or at least approximate) each value.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{95}\%\cdot{39}={37.05}</m></p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{38}\%\cdot{213}={80.94}</m></p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{2}\%\cdot{2488}={49.76}</m></p>
<p>From these calculations we see that 38<percent/> of 213 is the largest.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

